GOLDEN Arrows coach Steve Komphela during his time at Turkish Super League where he played for two Turkish sides, Gaziantepspor and Çanakkale Dardanelspor. In Turkey the former Bafana Bafana player, was also a TV presenter and hosted his own talk show on television channel Çanakkale Dardanelspor AS where he sang Turkish folk songs and told jokes. In one of interview Komphela had with a Sunday Paper in 2015, he admitted that his career as a TV presenter earned him more fame in Turkey, than his career as a footballer there. He stated: “I appeared on one TV show and people were surprised to hear a black man speak fluent Turkish, and that was how it really started. “I was subsequently given my own show by the owner of the television channel Canakkale Dardanelspor AS.”  